<html>  <head>    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=windows-1252">    <title>Exercises</title>  </head>  <body style="         background-color: WHITE;">    <p align="center"><font size="5">E<font size="4">XERCISES</font></font></p>    <div align="center">      <table width="90%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">        <tbody>          <tr>            <td>You should do as many of the following exercises as you can for              practice. Answers to most are in the back of your text. Some of              these problems will be used for the in-class quizzes and exam.<br>              <br>              Note that the exercises differ depending on what edition of the              text you are using. Regardless of the edition, the exercisies are              basically the same. They just have different numberings.</td>          </tr>        </tbody>      </table>      <br>      <div align="right">6.3&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>      <table bordercolordark="#666666" width="90%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"        bordercolor="#666666"        border="1">        <tbody>          <tr bgcolor="#CCCCCC">            <td rowspan="2" width="8%" valign="top">              <div align="right"><b>Section&nbsp;&nbsp;</b></div>            </td>            <td colspan="4">              <div align="center"><b>Exercises</b></div>            </td>          </tr>          <tr bgcolor="#CCCCCC">            <td width="24%" bgcolor="#DCF6D5" align="center"><em>Third Edition</em></td>            <td width="24%" bgcolor="#BAD9EB" align="center"> <b>&nbsp;<em>&nbsp;</em></b><em>Fifth
